## File Paths

### _modpath

```lua
+ OpenNetBattle
├─ ...
└─ resources
   └─ cards
      └─ example_card
         ├─ entry.lua
         └─ sub_folder
            └─ script.lua
```
This is a **`string`** containing the path to _the_ `entry.lua` _file for this package_.<br>
&emsp;i.e. For _all_ scripts in a mod, using `_modpath` _will_ give the same value.

_In the example on the right,_ `_modpath` _will always return `resources/cards/example_card/`.

### _folderpath

```lua
+ OpenNetBattle
├─ ...
└─ resources
   └─ cards
      └─ example_card
         ├─ entry.lua
         └─ sub_folder
            └─ script.lua
```
This is a **`string`** containing the path to _the current script file_.<br>
&emsp;i.e. For _all_ scripts in a mod, using `_modpath` _might not_ give the same value.

_In the example on the right,_ `_folderpath` _will return:_<br>
&emsp;In **`entry.lua`**: `resources/cards/example_card/`<br>
&emsp;In **`script.lua`**: `resources/cards/example_card/sub_folder/`.